title: Discovery-Expedition.Wreck.of.Bismarck.avi
description:
The German battleship Bismarck is one of the most famous warships of the Second World War. Named after the 19th century German chancellor Otto von Bismarck, Bismarck&#039;s fame came from the Battle of the Denmark Strait in May 1941, in which the battlecruiser HMS Hood, flagship and pride of the British Royal Navy, was sunk, from Churchill&#039;s subsequent order to "Sink the Bismarck" [1], and from the relentless pursuit by the Royal Navy that ended with her loss only three days later.

Have a nice day !
